it/fallback-router.vitest.ts`, `tests/unit/cli-matrix.vitest.ts` | Executor parsing, audit, fallback, and CLI dispatch behavior. |\n\n  Line 871: | DLR-003 | [F003 Fallback router](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router.md](01--executor/fallback-router.md) |\n\n  Line 912: | DLR-044 | [F042 Fallback-router typed reroute](../feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) | [01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md:\n  Line 39: - Feature catalog entry exists at `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`.\n\n  Line 43: 1. Inspect `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` for the implementation contract.\n\n  Line 44: 2. Inspect `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` for the matching regression coverage.\n\n  Line 68: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | typed fallback-router reroute + graph preflight. |\n\n  Line 74: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Primary regression coverage for Fallback-router typed reroute. |\n\n  Line 82: - Feature catalog entry: `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 83: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 84: - Source phase: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/030-deep-loop-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/015-fallback-router-typed-reroute`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router.md:\n  Line 39: - Feature catalog entry exists at `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md`.\n\n  Line 43: 1. Inspect `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` for the implementation contract.\n\n  Line 44: 2. Inspect `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` for the primary regression coverage.\n\n  Line 68: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Model registry lookup, fallback target selection, disabled fallback, and fail-fast reasons. |\n\n  Line 74: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Primary regression coverage for Fallback router. |\n\n  Line 82: - Feature catalog entry: `feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router.md`\n\n  Line 83: - Scenario file path: `manual_testing_playbook/01--executor/fallback-router.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 92: `lib/deep-loop/` holds the loop infrastructure. `executor-config` parses per-iteration executor settings from a shared schema so every consumer calls the same executor shape. `executor-audit` appends a provenance block to each iteration JSONL so you can tell which model and CLI produced each iteration. `prompt-pack` renders the iteration prompt template. `post-dispatch-validate` checks that an iteration produced valid markdown, JSONL and delta outputs before the state log accepts them, stamps seekable log-region offsets, and quarantines failed LLM-judge fallback cards. `atomic-state` writes state logs through a tmpfile-plus-rename pattern, adds compare-before-write, SHA-256 integrity helpers, and a deferred writer, so a crash never leaves a partial line and unchanged snapshots can avoid redundant writes. `jsonl-repair` recovers a corrupt trailing line before append and supports lock-held fan-out salvage merges. `loop-lock` enforces single-writer access around state mutations, with heartbeat metadata and opt-in host-local single-flight acquisition. `permissions-gate` checks permission scope before touching sensitive paths. `bayesian-scorer` exports the small Bayesian helpers `computeScore` and `shouldDemote`; `convergence.cjs` builds the typed loop decisions. `fallback-router` picks a replacement executor when the primary one times out and validates typed reroute graphs before dispatch.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/executor-audit.md:\n  Line 62: - [fallback-router.md](fallback-router.md) — Fallback router\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md:\n  Line 23: | [01--executor](01--executor/) | 4 features | `lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`, `lib/deep-loop/executor-audit.ts`, `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` |\n\n  Line 88: See [`01--executor/fallback-router.md`](01--executor/fallback-router.md) for full implementation and validation file listings.\n\n  Line 104: See [`01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`](01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md) for full implementation and validation file listings.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md:\n  Line 5:   - \"fallback-router typed reroute\"\n\n  Line 6:   - \"fallback-router-typed-reroute\"\n\n  Line 7:   - \"fallback-router typed reroute deep-loop-runtime\"\n\n  Line 8:   - \"executor fallback-router typed reroute\"\n\n  Line 40: | `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Runtime | typed fallback-router reroute + graph preflight. |\n\n  Line 46: | `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts` | Test | Primary regression coverage for Fallback-router typed reroute. |\n\n  Line 55: - Feature file path: `01--executor/fallback-router-typed-reroute.md`\n\n  Line 56: - Source phase: `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/030-deep-loop-improved/002-deep-loop-runtime/015-fallback-router-typed-reroute`\n\n  Line 57: - Primary sources: `lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`, `tests/unit/fallback-router.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/01--executor/fallback-router