ate-decision-matrix.md:\n  Line 31: Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs`, which the scenario identifies as runtime CLI script: three-state decision logic. Validation is anchored by `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts`, covering tests: \"allows convergence when ... thresholds are met\", \"continues convergence when non-blocking thresholds are not met\", \"blocks convergence for empty derived graphs...\".\n\n  Line 43: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Handler | runtime CLI script: three-state decision logic |\n\n  Line 44: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/council/council-graph-query.ts` | Library | Per-signal helpers (`agreementRatio`, `dissentDensity`, etc.) |\n\n  Line 52: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Tests: \"allows convergence when ... thresholds are met\", \"continues convergence when non-blocking thresholds are not met\", \"blocks convergence for empty derived graphs...\" |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/assets/deep_ai_council_config.json:\n  Line 37:     \"owner\": \"deep-loop-runtime\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/changelog/v1.12.0.0.md:\n  Line 1: This release rebinds deep-research onto the new `deep-loop-runtime` peer skill (arc 118, FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP). The 13 lib files plus the 4 graph operations (convergence, upsert, query, status) previously hosted inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` now live in `deep-loop-runtime/`. Deep-research workflow YAMLs invoke `.cjs` scripts directly instead of the removed `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools.\n\n  Line 11: Arc 118 (user-directive override of the 117 AI Council SPLIT ruling) consolidated all deep-loop runtime infrastructure into a new peer skill (`deep-loop-runtime`), deleted the 4 MCP tools, and switched the workflow YAML to direct `.cjs` script invocation — the same canonical pattern `reduce-state.cjs` already used. Operators tracing a deep-research bug now stay inside `deep-loop-runtime/` + `deep-research/` instead of traversing into a different skill's MCP server source tree.\n\n  Line 26: bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{session_id}\"'\n\n  Line 39: Any deep-research-adjacent code that previously imported from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/*` or `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/*` now imports from `deep-loop-runtime/lib/{deep-loop,coverage-graph}/*`. The SQLite database (`deep-loop-graph.sqlite`) moved with the schema-owner code and now lives at `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/storage/`.\n\n  Line 43: The `mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` include glob extended to discover tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts`, so a single `pnpm vitest run` exercises both surfaces. The only test that stayed in `mcp_server/tests/deep-loop/` is `review-depth-reducer.vitest.ts`, which tests `deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` (lives in `deep-review/`, not the migrated runtime).\n\n  Line 54: | `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` | MCP-tool invocations replaced with `bash: 'node .../deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<X>.cjs ...'`. |\n\n  Line 56: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/` (NEW peer skill) | All runtime infrastructure deep-research depends on. |\n\n  Line 60: No deep-research consumer changes required beyond what arc 118 shipped. Operators directly running `node deep-loop-runtime/scripts/<X>.cjs` should pass `--spec-folder`, `--loop-type`, `--session-id`, plus any optional flags documented in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/script_interface_contract.md`. The four `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` tools are gone and have no aliases; any external code that hardcoded those tool names must switch to the script paths.\n\n  Line 65: - **117 council ruling** (superseded): `.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/116-deep-skill-evolution/003-deep-loop-runtime/001-core-isolation-deliberation/decision-record.md`\n\n  Line 66: - **deep-loop-runtime v1.0.0 changelog**: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-tools-registered-separately-from-deep-loop.md:\n  Line 6:   - \"deep-loop-runtime --loop-type council\"\n\n  Line 19: Verify council graph operations no longer consume mk-spec-memory MCP tool slots and remain available through `deep-loop-runtime --loop-type council`.\n\n  Line 29: The shipped surface is anchored by `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/{upsert,query,status,convergence}.cjs --loop-type council`, plus `deep-ai-council/scripts/replay-graph-from-artifacts.cjs` for artifact replay. The playbook scenario `08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-tools-registered-separately-from-deep-loop.md` defines the operator prompt, command sequence, expected signals, evidence, and pass/fail criteria for DAC-026.\n\n  Line 31: Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tool-schemas.ts`, where the live registry now imports at 35 tools and has no council graph entries. Validation is anchored by `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts`, covering runtime script behavior for upsert, query, status, convergence, and error contracts.\n\n  Line 43: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/upsert.cjs` | Runtime CLI | Council node/edge projection writes |\n\n  Line 44: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs` | Runtime CLI | Council graph query modes |\n\n  Line 45: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/status.cjs` | Runtime CLI | Council readiness and recovery payload |\n\n  Line 46: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs` | Runtime CLI | Council convergence bridge fields |\n\n  Line 54: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | Automated test | Runtime council CLI coverage |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md:\n  Line 511: Related skills: `deep-review` for iterative audit loops, `deep-loop-runtime` for shared executor/state/coverage-graph runtime, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state, packet anchoring, and continuity saves.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/README.md:\n  Line 36: `Skill(deep-loop-workflows)` loads the hub, and the hub routes by `workflowMode` through `mode-registry.json` to one active mode packet. The hub holds no per-mode logic. Each packet keeps its own convergence math, state shape, artifacts and tool-permission guards. The shared backend, `deep-loop-runtime`, does the executor configuration, prompt-pack rendering, validation, atomic state, coverage graph and scoring.\n\n  Line 61: - **`runtimeLoopType`** is the graph-backed convergence key for `deep-loop-runtime`, one of `research`, `review` or `council` for active modes. It is an explicit `null` for the four improvement lanes and is never guessed from `workflowMode`.\n\n  Line 92: | `deep-loop-runtime` | The frozen, MCP-free backend the modes run on. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-ai-council/feature_catalog/08--council-graph-integration/council-graph-query-five-modes-prompt-safe-context.md:\n  Line 31: Current behavior is grounded in `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/query.cjs`, which the scenario