air: verify directional rule at every coupling site\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.85,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Directional-mechanics verification and the absolute/relative correction are net-new; mild overlap with iter 1 structural foundation.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Q2\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Q2\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Apply forward/reverse hop-math uniformly to every deep-loop-* string\",\"reason\":\"WRONG for absolute literals (F2.3); classify relative-require vs absolute-literal first\",\"evidence\":\"deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:15-288\"}],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"question\",\"id\":\"q2-coupling\",\"label\":\"Is the directional path-repair rule correct at every coupling site?\"},{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f2-1-reverse\",\"label\":\"Reverse rule (minus-one-hop, rename segment) confirmed correct\"},{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f2-2-forward\",\"label\":\"Forward rule (hop-unchanged, delete segment) confirmed correct\"},{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f2-3-absrel\",\"label\":\"CORRECTION: rule conflates absolute and relative paths\"},{\"type\":\"finding\",\"id\":\"f2-4-dense\",\"label\":\"compile-command-contracts.cjs is densest+highest-cascade forward site\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"from\":\"f2-1-reverse\",\"to\":\"q2-coupling\",\"relation\":\"ANSWERS\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"from\":\"f2-2-forward\",\"to\":\"q2-coupling\",\"relation\":\"ANSWERS\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"from\":\"f2-3-absrel\",\"to\":\"q2-coupling\",\"relation\":\"QUALIFIES\"}],\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T00:16:00Z\",\"durationMs\":480000}\n","filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/glm52-2/deep-research-state.jsonl"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unificat