y\": \"runtime-as-infrastructure (no graph-metadata.json, SKILL.md->README.md) correct\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F1.3\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CLARIFY\", \"run\": 1, \"summary\": \"Runtime doc families (feature_catalog/references/changelog/playbook) move as a unit\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F1.4\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"RISK\", \"run\": 1, \"severity\": \"low\", \"summary\": \"Two package.json under one skill; sanity-check package_skill --check\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F2.1\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CONFIRM\", \"run\": 2, \"summary\": \"Reverse rule (minus-one-hop, rename segment) correct\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F2.2\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CONFIRM\", \"run\": 2, \"summary\": \"Forward rule (hop-unchanged, delete segment) correct\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F2.3\", \"tier\": 1, \"type\": \"CORRECTION\", \"run\": 2, \"summary\": \"Rule conflates absolute and relative paths; absolutes need separate string-rename\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F2.4\", \"tier\": 1, \"type\": \"RISK\", \"run\": 2, \"severity\": \"medium\", \"summary\": \"compile-command-contracts.cjs densest (~36 paths) + hash-cascade; use as forward exit gate\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F2.5\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CONFIRM\", \"run\": 2, \"summary\": \"fanout-run.cjs:942-943 absolute forward path confirmed\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F3.1\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CONFIRM\", \"run\": 3, \"summary\": \"Forward borrow (tsc, @types); one-more-.. correct\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F3.2\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CONFIRM\", \"run\": 3, \"summary\": \"Reverse borrow (vitest glob); expansion correct\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F3.3\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CORRECTION\", \"run\": 3, \"summary\": \"Borrow surface ~6-8 sites, not 4\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F3.4\", \"tier\": 1, \"type\": \"RISK\", \"run\": 3, \"severity\": \"medium\", \"summary\": \"memory-runtime-retention.vitest.ts:9 active import = hard failure post-move, not silent hole\" },\n    { \"id\": \"F3.5\", \"tier\": 3, \"type\": \"CLARIFY\", \"run\": 3, \"summary\": \"Borrow has two